# Frontend Rules

**Layers:** Pages → Hooks → Services → Components.

| Concern | Lives in |
|---------|----------|
| Routing / page composition | `src/app/` |
| Business logic, side effects, IPC calls | `src/lib/hooks/` |
| Tauri `invoke` wrappers (Zod-validated) | `src/lib/ipc/` |
| Sidecar HTTP/SSE clients | `src/lib/ai/` |
| Zustand slices (one per domain) | `src/lib/store/` |
| Domain entity classes | `src/lib/domain/` |
| Shared types | `src/lib/types/` |
| Reusable presentational UI | `src/components/` |
| shadcn primitives (auto-generated) | `src/components/ui/` |

## Prohibited

- Business logic in components. No `if` branches on domain state beyond rendering — extract to a hook.
- `invoke()` or `fetch()` inside a component. Always go through `src/lib/ipc/` or `src/lib/ai/`.
- Direct mutation of Zustand state from a component. Components call hook-exposed actions.
- `any` / `unknown` without a type guard or Zod parse.
- Hardcoded colors / sizes / user-facing strings. Use Tailwind tokens (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`) and i18n keys.
- Default exports (except `vite.config.ts` and other framework config).
- Native HTML elements when a shadcn primitive exists (`<Button>`, `<Input>`, `<Dialog>`).

## Required

- Named exports only.
- Components are pure functions of props + subscribed store selectors.
- Hooks own all side effects (`useEffect`, `useQuery`, `useMutation`, store subscriptions, event listeners).
- Icon-only buttons must have `aria-label` or wrap a `<Tooltip>`.
- Pages wrapped in the standard layout shell (sidebar / main / right panel).

## Limits (lines, hard ceilings)

- Component: **150**. Page: **200**. Hook: **80**. Slice: **150**. Service: **150**.

## Reactive OO pattern

Domain entities are classes (`Project`, `Package`, `ProcessHandle`). They expose methods that mutate internal state. A Zustand slice owns the instance and re-emits selectors. Components subscribe via `useStore(selector)`.

```ts
// src/lib/domain/process-handle.ts
export class ProcessHandle {
  private _status: ProcessStatus = 'starting';
  get status() { return this._status; }
  restart(): void { /* ... */ }
}

// src/lib/store/processes-slice.ts — owns the map of handles
// src/lib/hooks/use-process.ts — exposes restart() as a stable callback
// src/components/processes/process-tab.tsx — renders status, calls onRestart
```

Components never `new ProcessHandle()` and never call `handle.restart()` directly — they invoke a callback returned by the hook.
